

- Serialization and Deserialization

- Reasons for this vulnerability to exist and working of logical flaws.

Tip: Learning is best done through Analogies(Comparing and differentiating with one another)

- Objects are made of 2 things:
	- State (Type)
	- Behaviour (Property)

- The cookies that are asked by websites... Are actually user-specific behaviour tokens... These are stored to track what you visit the most or what you like, what content you share... And all that kind of crap. 
	- Therefore allowing cookies to the site, is like allowing them to record your visits and likes... You can disable cookies on a site, but then that might make the web-app work unexpectedly.

